This paper deals with image attractiveness ranking using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a web image index and a commercial search engine, indicating a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of judges and their personal preferences, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a deep convolutional neural network and rank net, which are machine learning techniques, indicating a possible connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
